# Windsurf Profile for ZinTrust Workspace
# Based on .vscode/settings.json and extensions.json

## Core Development Environment

### TypeScript & JavaScript Support
- Use TypeScript 5.x with strict mode enabled
- Enable all inlay hints for better code understanding
- Auto-import suggestions should be enabled
- Format on save using Prettier
- ESLint should run on type and fix issues automatically

### Code Quality Standards
- ESLint rules must be followed (no warnings, no errors)
- Prettier formatting with 2-space indentation
- Maximum line length: 80 characters (soft), 100 (medium), 120 (hard)
- No trailing whitespace
- Files must end with newline
- Auto-organize imports on save

### Testing Requirements
- Use Vitest for unit testing
- Test files should follow pattern: *.test.ts or *.test.js
- Tests must be isolated and not share state
- Mock implementations should avoid nested callbacks (>3 levels)
- All tests must pass before commits

### File Structure & Patterns
- Use TypeScript for all new files
- Follow existing naming conventions (PascalCase for classes, camelCase for variables)
- Environment files: .env, .env.example (dotenv syntax)
- Config files: *.config.ts (TypeScript)
- Docker: docker-compose.yml (YAML), Dockerfile (dockerfile)

