## Project-Specific Rules

### ORM & Database
- Use Model.define() for model definitions
- Relationship methods must follow naming conventions
- Eager loading to prevent N+1 queries
- All database operations must be type-safe

### Security & Validation
- Environment variables must be validated on startup
- Use TypeScript strict mode for security
- Input validation for all user data
- Secret management with proper validation

### Testing Strategy
- Unit tests for business logic
- Integration tests for database operations
- Mock external dependencies
- Test coverage requirements
- No nested callbacks in tests (>3 levels)

